Find: Support searching by name and/or module
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command can only search by name.

By allowing module searching, users can save time and find contacts
easier depending on their motive. Users can also chain module codes
and names to be more specific in their search.

Let's,
* update the search algorithm to tokenize the argument to search for
  specific fields
* update the name predicate class to accommodate for more fields
* update the test methods to verify the correctness of the changes

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix edit command where user input with only location field provided does not edit successfully
Find: Support searching by all fields
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command can only search by name and module code.

By allowing all fields to be specified, users can narrow down their
search as much as they want. Additionally, searching by tags can be
chained to find only persons who match all the given tags.

Let's,
* update the search algorithm to tokenize the argument to search for all
  fields
* update the name predicate class to accommodate for all fields
